          <msContents>
            <summary>Assignment of power of attorney by Luigi di Antonio de Covoni, Florentine merchant acting on behalf of himself and of his business partner Lorenzo di Giovanni Amadori, to Gherardo Lanaiolo, also of Florence. Notarized by Bartolomeo di Antonio di San Miniato on 7 June 1422, in the presence of the witnesses Francesco di Giovanni Trenta, Stefano Paoli, and Arrigo di Bartolomeo da Tonda. Filed with the document is a short, later summary written in Italian on paper.</summary>
